Introduction

An Da Eun, or An Daeun, is a South Korean singer-songwriter and co-founder of the agency ADE Music. She is the vocalist of the duo, The ADE, that formed in July 2016.

Before this, she was the vocalist of the duo Acoustic Collabo from August 2011 to June 2016. She also debuted as a soloist on November 20, 2020, with the digital single "I Was Young and I Wanted to Say I Was Sorry”. She also competed on JTBC’s 2021/2022 survival show “Sing Again 2” as Singer No. 48 and made it to the top 26.
